                    <div class="SWWW_Grid SWWW_Grid5050">
                        <div>
                            <p class="SWWW_P">Sustainable WWW was founded in 2021 by Michael Andersen with a clear mission: to reduce the environmental impact of the internet. It all started as a blog where Michael shared his research and practical advice on making web development more sustainable. The blog quickly gained traction, leading to a newsletter, podcast appearances, and the publication of the book <a href="/en/sustainable-web-design-in-20-lessons">Sustainable Web Design in 20 Lessons</a>.</p>
                            <p>In 2023, the project took a major step forward with the launch of Wiki—an open-source library of sustainable web practices, hosted on GitHub and preserved in the Arctic Vault for future generations.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <p class="SWWW_P">Today, Sustainable WWW is an international company helping clients in Sweden, Denmark, Norway, and various English-speaking countries build sustainable websites. Our mission remains the same—to make the internet more optimized and durable in alignment with global sustainability goals. At the same time, we ensure your websites and web applications meet your business objectives and requirements.</p>
                        </div>
